ing International, Inc.}}\n* Original Langster\n* [[3 Arts Entertainment]]\n* [[Universal Television]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Netflix]]\n| budget                   = \n| network                  = Netflix\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = <!-- The nation in which the series first aired, if different from country parameter -->\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|4|27}}\n| last_aired               = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| website                  = <!-- Remove or comment out this parameter line completely if URL exists on or is moved to Wikidata; use |website_title= to change the display title. -->\n| production_website       = <!-- use |production_website_title= to change the display title. -->\n}}\n'''''Never Have I Ever''''' is an American [[coming of age]] [[dramedy]] television series on [[Netflix]] starring [[Tamil Canadian]] actress [[Maitreyi Ramakrishnan]] and created by [[Mindy Kaling]] and Lang Fisher. It premiered on April 27, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/tv-news-roundup-netflix-releases-trailer-mindy-kalings-never-have-i-ever-1234581321/|title=TV News Roundup: Netflix Releases 'Never Have I Ever' Trailer (Watch)|last=Shafer|first=Ellise|date=April 15, 2020|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/ramakrishnan-mindy-kaling-netflix-1.5265663|title='Be that change': Maitreyi Ramakrishnan on starring in Mindy Kaling's new comedy|date=August 30, 2019|work=CBC|access-date=April 16, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/watch-mindy-kaling-never-have-i-ever-trailer-netflix.html|title=Dear Gods, Meet Devi, a Young Mindy Kaling in Netflix's Never Have I Ever|last=Murphy|first=Chris|date=April 15, 2020|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><r